This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category as it deals with the recovery of a MediaWiki grammar, which is a natural language processing task. It also involves the use of multiple syntactic notations, which is a common technique in computational linguistics. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it mentions the use of semi-automatic extraction techniques. 

The Software Engineering (cs.SE) category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the problems encountered in grammars that were not engineered properly. 

The Programming Languages (cs.PL) category is relevant as the paper deals with the transformation of a grammar, which is a fundamental concept in programming languages. 

Finally, the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category is a possibility as the paper involves the use of automated techniques to extract a grammar from a community-created text.
